ed. I need to ensure that my edits to X509 are reflected in the reports and figure out a test to catch any exceptions properly. Let's inspect this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying native compile issues**\\n\\nI'm noticing that if the `getConstructor` call fails, then `Constructor#newInstance` isn't covered. It seems the dynamic access compile manages to cover new instances due to static analysis. The reflection calls are generated during native compile instrumentation, but I wonder if the coverage report is outdated. The user likely wants a fix for the native failure and coverage. I might need to pick the `X509` class, but I should consider a safer option that has reflection metadata. I’ll need to dig deeper into this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring build-time resolution**\\n\\nI’m considering how `Class.getConstructor` calls can be resolved at build time in a Native Image context, particularly with constant arguments. It turns out that native-image can detect reflection calls automatically. However, in `BaseSecretKeyFactory`, the `keySpec` is a method parameter, which might complicate things. Since it previously failed in the Raw test, I'm unsure if this will work. I should look into `X509EncodedKeySpec` and maybe also consider using `PKCS8EncodedKeySpec` for a similar purpose. Let’s make a decision!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `BaseSecretKeyFactoryTest` to avoid reflecting on Bouncy Castle’s `RawEncodedKeySpec`, which failed under Native Image due missing constructor metadata.\n\nThe test now requests a JDK key spec instead:\n\n- Uses `X509EncodedKeySpec.class`\n- Still drives `BaseSecretKeyFactory.engineGetKeySpec`\n- Still reaches the generic reflective path:\n  - `Class#getConstructor(byte[].class)`\n  - `Constructor#newInstance(...)`\n- Verifies the returned key spec format and encoded key bytes\n\nChanged file:\n\n`tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BaseSecretKeyFactoryTest.java`\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07682197761587bf016a25eff1b6908196a75d6ddb5128bc1f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 632, "output": 1684, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51468, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780871119124, "responseId": "resp_07682197761587bf016a25efcfc8188196917c55b4b45cc588"}, "toolResults": []}
